== Chiefdom of Magu<U+00E1> ==
[[Image:Magu<U+00E1>.JPG|thumb|300px|right|chiefdoms in Magu<U+00E1>]]
The cacique of Magu<U+00E1> (''cacicazgo Magu'') was on the whole northeastern part of Hispaniola, bordered to the north and east by the Atlantic Ocean, the south by the caciques of Maguana and Hig<U+00FC>ey, and west by the caciques of Mari<U+00E9>n and Maguana. This chiefdom covered only the territories of the current Dominican Republic.

It was ruled by the cacique [[Guarionex]], which is headquartered near the present location of [[Santo Cerro]] in [[La Vega (city)|La Vega]]. It was divided into 21 nita<U+00ED>nos. This cacique was one of the richest regions of the island.

Magua has the meaning: "the Stone" and his mother-goddess was ''Guacara'' or the 'Stone Mother'.

