== Chiefdom of Hig<U+00FC>ey ==
[[Image:Hig<U+00FC>ey.JPG|thumb | 300px | right | chiefdoms Hig<U+00FC>ey]]
The cacique of Hig<U+00FC>ey (''cacicazgo Hig<U+00FC>ey'') spanned the entire southeast of Hispaniola, bordered to the north by the cacique of Magu<U+00E1> and the [[Bay Samana]], south by the Caribbean, east by the [[Canal de la Mona]], and west by the cacique of Maguana and Magu<U+00E1>. This cacique only covered the territories of the current Dominican Republic.

It was ruled by the cacique [[Cayacoa]]. Its headquarters was located in present-day [[Hig<U+00FC>ey (city)|Hig<U+00FC>ey]]. This cacique extended from [[Cabo Enga<U+00F1>o]] to the river [[Haina (river)|Haina]]. It was divided into 21 nita<U+00ED>nos. This cacique is also known as the '''Hig<U+00FC>anamo'''.

The mother goddess of Hig<U+00FC>ey was Atabeira, which means "Mother of the original stone".

